# --- BEGINNER EXPLANATION ---
# 1. What is a .env file?
# It stores environment variables (secret or environment-specific config). 
# This file should never be committed to GitHub for security reasons.
# 
# 2. Why PORT?
# The PORT specifies which port our Node.js server will listen on.
# 
# 3. Why MongoDB URI?
# The MONGO_URI tells our backend exactly where the database is running locally.
# 127.0.0.1 refers to your "localhost" (your own machine).
# 27017 is the default port for MongoDB.
# /todoapp is the name of the database that will be created automatically.
